{"commentv2": 1, "number": 6, "id": 2449167, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "mist3h", "body": "Monk healers should [u]not use[/u] [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=198664/invoke-chi-ji-the-red-crane]Invoke Chi-Ji, the Red Crane[/url] during this encounter (specifically during Flame Wreath).\r\nThose cranes running to players will cause the Flame Wreath to explode and wipe your group. It shouldn't be this way, but it is.", "date": "2016-11-28T07:49:21-06:00", "rating": 6, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 7, "id": 2462656, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "Shoshin", "body": "A useful couple of things we found after wondering why we were wiping when no-one was moving on [spell=228261]\n\n[ol]\n[li]Hunter pets will cause [spell=228261] to trigger.  Our hunter changed from BM to MM to counter this. [/li]\n[li]If you have more than 1 melee, and if they each get a [spell=228261], even if they don't move the flame wreath just blows up if the circles of flame wreath overlap. [/li]\n[li]For you druids....skull bash moves you forward.  Guess what that triggers if it's there?  That's right!  [spell=228261]. Sorry guildies, that wipe's on me :)[/li]\n[/ol]\n\nFor point 2, we saw when the cast for the special ability was coming (one of [spell=228261], [spell=227779] or [spell=228334], the melee just ran away and spread out until we saw what the cast was. \n\nHope this helps a few people!", "date": "2017-01-13T09:45:30-06:00", "rating": 7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Do you know if there's any way to tell *who* triggered the explosion? I'm combing through combat log, and can't figure it out. I know on one wipe, it was me as guardian druid using skull bash, a couple of times I suspect it might have been the warlock interrupt pet (demon dog thing), and a few times, we're not entirely sure (so I'm guessing it might have been the melee too close together thing). So frustrating. Sigh.", "creationdate": "2017-01-20T14:06:16-06:00", "id": 1026481, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2462656, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Knitten", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "We couldn't figure out who triggered ours either. We had a complete guess that with the melee too close it's actually the flames moving which triggered flame wreath, but that's pure guesswork. Hence we ran away. We lost some DPS with this, but we didn't wipe! Agreed though. It was frustrating! EDIT: Note the warlock pet - did you try without the pet up too? It's very likely warlock pets have the same trigger as hunter pets?", "creationdate": "2017-01-22T09:22:43-06:00", "id": 1027084, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2462656, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Shoshin", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Do not use [spell=198013] either...", "creationdate": "2018-05-26T18:17:29-05:00", "id": 1113981, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2462656, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Sayatin", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2017-01-13T09:51:32-06:00", 2, "Shoshin"]}
