{"commentv2": 1, "number": 9, "id": 389289, "nreplies": 5, "sticky": 0, "user": "Ayline", "body": "Medivh was the \"Last Guardian of Tirisfal.\" His home was Karazan. When he was in his mother's(Aegwynn's) womb, she killed Sargeras' physical body and locked it away where the Maelstorm now is. When Sargeras's physical form was killed he planted a \"seed\" in Aegwynn. The seed implanted itself into Medivh. Aegwynn did know and passed the powers of the Guardian to Medivh as a baby. When Medivh was 14 the powers awakened and Medivh's body put itself in a coma to prevent him from dying.\nWhen Medivh awoke Sargeras took control until Medivh \"died\" and was cleansed of the demon when he returned. While Sargeras was in control he performed such acts as introducing the Orcs of Draenor to demonic magic. He also assisted them in opening the gate to Azeroth.\nWhen Medivh regained control after \"dying\" he set forth the exodus of humans and orcs to Kalimdor to escape the Scourge. Medivh also set forth in motion the events leading to the temporary alliance between the Humans and Orcs and the permanent alliance between Night Elves and Humans.\n\n(If I have anything wrong, i'll be glad to fix, just let me know.)", "date": "2008-09-27T00:17:17-05:00", "rating": 25, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "You asked for some things about Medivh's life, well here are a few things...  1) Med's mom wasnt pregnant with him yet. Sargeras snuck into her body, and then when Medivh was concieved, he entered his fetus.  2) Sargeras' tomb isnt in the Maelstrom. Its in an island that was raised by Gul'Dan, assumed to be off the coast of Khaz'modan or Lorderaon.  3) When Medivh fell into a coma, it was because Sargeras shut his body down, due to the emergence of the tirisfalen magic.  4) Medivh DID die, and then later, after the second war, his mother ressurected him.  5) Medivh didnt show the Orcs demon ma", "creationdate": "2008-09-27T00:17:18-05:00", "id": 362579, "rating": 19, "commentid": 389289, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "243538", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Sargeras's Tomb actually IS in the Maelstrom, play the first three missions of the Night Elf campaign in WC3: The Frozen Throne.  The Island Illidan raised housed the Tomb of Sargeras, which is where Illidan got the Eye of Sargeras.", "creationdate": "2009-01-12T22:31:13-06:00", "id": 72344, "rating": 6, "commentid": 389289, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "302936", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Because what kind of mom would fight Sargeras while pregnant?", "creationdate": "2009-08-18T22:57:48-05:00", "id": 117073, "rating": 6, "commentid": 389289, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "129750", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "A really badass mom.", "creationdate": "2009-11-04T15:57:42-06:00", "id": 130723, "rating": 38, "commentid": 389289, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "258919", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "She didn't fight him pregnant. He hung out in her womb until she conceived, and then corrupted Medivh.", "creationdate": "2012-02-25T23:51:19-06:00", "id": 522719, "rating": 0, "commentid": 389289, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Saerise", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-09-27T00:20:40-05:00", 1, "Ayline"]}
