{"commentv2": 1, "number": 5, "id": 1624906, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "ShadowHMF", "body": "\"To pass beyond my Hall, you must defeat me in a game of [u][b]skill![/b][/u] Control your king when you are ready to begin...\" - Echo of Medivh\n\nYet what I don't get is, why does he cheat when he wants a game of skill :)", "date": "2012-02-11T10:55:18-06:00", "rating": 38, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "He knows you wont cheat. Thinks you will play fair. Considers intruders (us) fools.", "creationdate": "2016-04-07T15:41:29-05:00", "id": 937351, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1624906, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Pypode", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2012-02-11T11:12:49-06:00", 1, "ShadowHMF"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 6, "id": 1705552, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "jdevlin7756", "body": "I'm hoping this is just a bug... but as of patch day 5.0.4 this event is no longer possible.  Please understand, I've been doing solo Kara for months now (DE and gold drops.... easy 45mins) .  The event now happens so fast that I don't think it's possible with a full raid.\n\n*edit: It is still possible... It just takes a LOT of tries until Medivh finally hands you the fight by standing his king in fire or some such.  Even still I just BARELY won.", "date": "2012-08-29T02:04:10-05:00", "rating": 6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Also just did this in 5.0.4, but as a duo. Echo of Medivh would cheat within one move of the start and then continue to cheat nearly every move. There was a time during our second attempt that 9 squares on our back two rows were on fire and it simply wasn't possible to move the king (or the clerics) out of it. We just gave up after the fourth attempt since we were just doing it for rep (already have the achieve), but this is definitely much different than it has been for the last couple of months.", "creationdate": "2012-08-29T20:40:17-05:00", "id": 567239, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1705552, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "shadowtwinX", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2012-08-30T11:16:17-05:00", 3, "jdevlin7756"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 7, "id": 1844608, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "506887", "body": "Currently, Hunter's exhiliration talent can heal the King while in the \"vehicle\" as it were.\n\nEdit: Coupled with Readiness, this allowed me to heal him back to full twice, even after getting crappy luck with placement I won first try.", "date": "2013-04-18T10:29:16-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "This is still the case as of 5.4. Exhilaration is the best way to solo as a hunter. If you don't have it learned, the vendor just outside the hall has the tome/dust so you can learn it on the spot.", "creationdate": "2013-11-07T18:07:05-06:00", "id": 706473, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1844608, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Mulder101361", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "This is no longer the case since 7.0", "creationdate": "2016-08-11T19:09:17-05:00", "id": 959422, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1844608, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Kodyack", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Nope...this still works, even in 8.0.1. That's how i was doing it always. If Medivh cheats, i cheat also :P.", "creationdate": "2018-11-12T11:31:12-06:00", "id": 1203040, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1844608, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "niqushortz", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2013-04-18T10:47:35-05:00", 1, "506887"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 8, "id": 1855904, "nreplies": 14, "sticky": 0, "user": "1062573", "body": "I used to have trouble with the chess event but found a strategy that was easily crushing the opponent (to the point that I'm ending the game with 8 pieces alive, all of theirs dead). I should note this is a combination of things I've seen from other people combined together with a few things of my own, but I don't see any info on it on wowhead, so I figured I'd post it.\r\n\r\nMake sure game sound is on, at least at the start, as you will be wanting to listen to an audio queu from Medivh.\r\n\r\n1) Start the game by activating your king and spam the leave vehicle button.\r\n2) Activate the pawn in front of the king as soon as possible (you can spam click it and hit escape if the say option isn't up yet), move it ahead one space, and get out as quickly as possible (don't even wait for the piece to finish moving, just hit move and get out of there).\r\n3) Take one of your pawns which is one from the end (i.e. in front of the knight) and move it ahead one space. Get out as fast as possible.\r\n\r\n--------- Here's where the real strategy starts ----------------\r\n\r\n4) Grab the Rook near the second pawn you moved and get it somewhere into the center as soon as possible.\r\n5) The goal is to exploit is Hellfire (aoe) ability. Spam is absolutely as much as possible. It has an aoe radius of 2, so position for maximum damage.\r\n6) First priority should be to wipe out large clumps of Footman\r\n7) Second priority, and something you do need to do, is to kill both of the enemy's healers, though you may have to do it one at a time.\r\n8) Try to position your Rook so it can melee a piece, preferably a healer when possible. The aoe is his main mechanic, but the melee damage will help on stronger pieces.\r\n9) Avoid taking too much damage on the Rook. In particular, keep moving him around so that he's not getting punched by enemy pieces. Remember that you don't have to \"run away\" from a piece to avoid getting hit, you just need to move to a direction they're not facing.\r\n\r\n--------- Medivh Cheating ----------------\r\n\r\n10) Medivh will cheat, but he'll have an audio queu before he activates the mechanic about evening the field. The first cheat will always be fire. The very moment you hear the queu, get out of your Rook and head to your King. You should be able to get him out of the fire only taking a few ticks. He won't do fire again.\r\n11) Throughout the fight, Medivh will empower units. You CANNOT let anything important (Rooks, Kings, or Queen) get meleed by these units. Even if it's just an enemy pawn, they hit INCREDIBLY hard when empowered, and will tear anything they melee apart.\r\n\r\n---------- Endgame ---------------\r\n\r\n12) To win, you need to clear much of the enemy's field (well, not technically, but it will help a lot). You do need to kill the enemy's healers.\r\n13) Use your judgement, but expend your Rooks first. Their aoe is incredibly powerful and they can do a lot of damage. After almost all enemy units are dead, their aoe isn't so great, which makes them good fodder for meleeing the enemy healers to death.\r\n14) You will want to end the game using the Queen. Unlike many strats, you will never actually be piloting the King; moving him forward tends to get him killed a lot when you can't control your healers at the same time. The Queen should first be picking off the remaining enemy healer (if both healers are up and at high health, you need to do better work with your Rooks). Once the enemy healers are dead, just focus on the King and he will fall. The Queen can attack from VERY far away, nuking the king down without even getting in his danger range. If he decides to stay on the far side of the field, your Queen nukes him down without taking any damage; if he comes in close, you should still have half a dozen units up that will pile damage onto him.\r\n\r\nFINAL NOTE: Do NOT, I repeat, do NOT just pull out a Rook and leave it there. You want to manually control them. If you leave the AI to do it's own thing, it will not Hellfire nearly enough. Furthermore, the AI is not smart enough to \"evade\" enemies. You want to keep trying to move the Rook around everytime enemy pieces are meleeing it, not to mention moving to where your aoe will do more damage. A single piloted Rook is 10 times more effective than 2 unpiloted Rooks moved to the center of the field. Other than saving your King from fire or empowered pieces, you should always be in the Rooks until either the enemy board has been cleared or both the Rooks are dead.", "date": "2013-05-22T12:32:22-05:00", "rating": 93, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Excellent strategy, worked straight away for me.", "creationdate": "2013-11-10T19:09:22-06:00", "id": 707110, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1855904, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "UberRob", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "A bit convoluted, but worked first try. Nicely done :)", "creationdate": "2013-11-30T18:53:42-06:00", "id": 711643, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1855904, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Ishm", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "This worked very well. It's not a magic cheat or anything, but it's a good strategy. Worked the second try. (First try I killed everything else, but didn't get to the healers. Sirinad is not kidding about that part.) Just stay alert and watch the board!", "creationdate": "2014-03-03T07:00:39-06:00", "id": 732547, "rating": 4, "commentid": 1855904, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Derannimer", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Excellet! This should be the top comment. Not the useless comments up there... u.u", "creationdate": "2014-05-07T00:26:43-05:00", "id": 744520, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1855904, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "skeltcher", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "The strategy described by sirinad works, but since English is only my second language and I haven't played chess that much I wasn't sure of all the pieces mentioned. Looked it up and put it up here in the hope someone else finds it useful: King = [npc=21684] / [npc=21752], Pawn = [npc=17211] / [npc=17469], Knight = [npc=21664] / [npc=21748], Rook = [npc=21160] / [npc=21726], Bishop (Healer) = [npc=21682] / [npc=21747], Queen = [npc=21683] / [npc=21750]", "creationdate": "2017-02-11T06:36:05-06:00", "id": 1031849, "rating": 20, "commentid": 1855904, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Sodal", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 9, "id": 1859313, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "WatashiFR", "body": "Since 5.3 the doors eventually open automatically regardless if you complete the Chess Event or not. You do have to make an effort though.", "date": "2013-05-28T16:29:05-05:00", "rating": -10, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "This simply isn't true.", "creationdate": "2013-06-14T13:33:26-05:00", "id": 669061, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1859313, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "buhbull", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I've observed it happen. Started the event, failed it and restarted, then at some point (I'm not quite sure after how much time) the doors just opened even though the warchief was still up.", "creationdate": "2013-06-23T06:41:33-05:00", "id": 671575, "rating": -1, "commentid": 1859313, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "WatashiFR", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 10, "id": 1987308, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Shawnyall", "body": "So it took me a while to understand how to perform any aforementioned strategies, but once I figured out how this chess works (because the Leave Vehicle button wouldn't work on my bars), I finished it on my first try WITHOUT ANY REAL STRATEGY.\r\n\r\nSo, instead of doing any of that confusing junk, I just let the game progress while I tried to figure out how to exit the king. \r\n\r\nAfter a while, it was only my king, two clerics, a charger, and the mage. I let the charger tank the Warchief and use the mage as RDPS, buffing them both with my King and healing the charger with my Cleric. The charger soon died, and I had my King tank and DPS the Warchief, switching between the cleric and mage for more DPS and heals, and the Warchief went down without any problems.\r\n\r\nAll the strategy, I'd say, is just malarky. It's easier to wing it than to follow instructions.", "date": "2014-08-02T02:47:21-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
