{"commentv2": 1, "number": 12, "id": 2213260, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "jedizombies", "body": "If you find your \"Leave Vehicle\" button on your bars not working, try right clicking the buff off. My 'Leave Vehicle\" button never works, but removing the buff helps me leave the piece I chose so I can hop in another one. \r\n\r\nHope this helps. :)", "date": "2015-07-13T16:36:30-05:00", "rating": 8, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 13, "id": 2234696, "nreplies": 5, "sticky": 0, "user": "tibbyjudy", "body": "My very simple strategy:\r\n\r\n1) Hop in the king to start the battle, hop out as quick as possible.\r\n\r\n2) get in the warlock (horde) or the conjurer (alliance).\r\n\r\n3) Spam 3 and 4 every time a piece gets within range. \r\n\r\n4) The other king will eventually walk over towards you and you'll be able to nuke him down.\r\n\r\nNote: This isn't a strategy that will work every time, but since I've been farming Karazhan it's worked every time for me within 3 tries. Also, very low maintenance! No panicking!", "date": "2015-08-19T22:00:18-05:00", "rating": 12, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Easiest method EVER, straight to the king. works 90% of the time.", "creationdate": "2016-08-17T06:11:56-05:00", "id": 961165, "rating": 3, "commentid": 2234696, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "schmilblick", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Only tried it once (today) and it worked just fine.", "creationdate": "2016-08-25T11:01:40-05:00", "id": 963133, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2234696, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Xweaz", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "This still works pretty good. Tried it today and it worked first try. You just have to move out of the fire or away from buffed enemy pawns/warlocks with your conjurer/warlock. --- Also, as mentioned somewhere above, IF YOU'RE USING ELVUI - deactivate it for this fight or else your king will be gone.", "creationdate": "2018-01-13T18:07:18-06:00", "id": 1093851, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2234696, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Bisquit", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Best strategy ever, and so simple.", "creationdate": "2018-04-22T07:51:49-05:00", "id": 1109496, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2234696, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Uregale", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I had to take out the healers first, but after that it worked on the first try", "creationdate": "2020-08-10T19:27:15-05:00", "id": 1383547, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2234696, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Sunnygirl9876", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
