{"commentv2": 1, "number": 15, "id": 2356379, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Zemia", "body": "This was on Horde side but I could only control the Warchief.  I spammed bloodlust till a decent amount of the ally side pieces were dead. The King moved to the middle of the board and my warlocks were lighting him up.  I was able to move in front of the pawn that was in front of me, the circle indicating were you move to was only partially in that space but I was still able to move there.  I continued to bloodlust and cleave on the King and down he went. Took about 5ish minutes I'd guess. Hope this helps someone, I only did it once so far.", "date": "2016-07-24T17:35:26-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 16, "id": 2357948, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "ladorna", "body": "I do not know if this is a glitch with the Legion Pre-Patch but when i did the chess event this week, the horde pieces moved forward and then turned their backs to me. Also, their \"king\" never moved until i attacked him. Sure made the event much easier.", "date": "2016-07-27T20:44:40-05:00", "rating": 15, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I came here to ask if this had been nerfed! Was soloing Karazhan today and literally all I had to do was hop into the king, slowly walk over to the other king (who was just standing by himself twiddling his thumbs) and hit him with my hammer until he died. Bam, victory in about 1 minute. Was wondering if it had to do with me being level 100, but it sounds like it's been nerfed definitely.", "creationdate": "2016-08-03T02:08:42-05:00", "id": 956741, "rating": 2, "commentid": 2357948, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "LeaNoodles", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I believe they now turn off boss mechanics that are meant for several players if there are only a couple people in the raid, not sure though.", "creationdate": "2016-09-07T17:57:16-05:00", "id": 971477, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2357948, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Quizzeh", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 17, "id": 2366178, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Viscario", "body": "Note about chess event: sometimes the pieces you control and move forward face the direction you moved from, as in turn their backs to the enemy. This takes up precious time so best course is to move two pawns from the front of your king and queen a step forward, move one of the horses (and the equivalent on Horde side) to the front of the queen, making sure it faces the enemy. This gives the queen more time to live and deal damage to the enemy pieces.\r\n\r\nFinally, take control of your king, spawn buff but don't move until Medivh uses the fire cheat. Otherwise wait for the enemy king to move to you to kill him while clearing the board out of other pieces.\r\n\r\nTested multiple times on Alliance side during pre-patch and works, even though the need to turn those pawns facing the enemy again is a bit annoying.", "date": "2016-08-12T11:00:50-05:00", "rating": 6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 18, "id": 2493701, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Enina", "body": "I've been running through this place a lot lately attempting to snag Midnight and all 3 Illusions (just missing Soulfrost now), but I stop on Chess to grab a few items I've missed on my non-DHs.\r\n\r\nThe most successful I've been is dragging out the Rook and Knight on one side and pushing through. The knight can easily get to the backline, while the rook can AoE many enemies at once and/or distract them. The main goal is to kill at least one Bishop (healer). With both up, they will spam heal the king and you can't burn him down. However, with one dead and other troops engage, you can typically overwhelm the king pretty easily--you might need to back off to get a heal on him once or twice.\r\n\r\nPosition your king to engage, or manually control him if you want, but I recommend using your queen to decimate from range. Their range is massive, and their damage is extremely high. As long as your king is not disproportionately low or somehow surrounded, you can pretty much snipe down their king at your leisure. You really don't need to control your grunts (maybe one or two at most), and only one side of your board to be effective. You can position your bishops facing your targets and they will spam damage when not healing.\r\n\r\nChess isn't hard solo, but it's tedious. Medivh's cheating is annoying, but not really terrible. Even if you somehow lose a piece to his fire or super saiyan buffs, you can still complete this with relative ease.", "date": "2017-05-11T09:06:42-05:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "This one helped me. Basically I let the Rook backline for pawns killing off other pawns with aoe and RNG shifted in my favor when the enemy healer came to me and the other healer pretty much did the same thing. As this was my second attempt at doing this boss, both were won successfully after their healers were down. Since the enemy king loves getting up close and personal, it was easily gg for me.", "creationdate": "2017-07-31T03:28:40-05:00", "id": 1065250, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2493701, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Illmatica", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 19, "id": 2513176, "nreplies": 4, "sticky": 0, "user": "hunnib", "body": "What not to do when trying to solo the chess game. \r\n\r\nYou must hop into the king to start, and his icon appears under yours, like hunter pet. My red dismount arrow was no where to be found and I did not see a buff I could click off. I right clicked on the king's icon and dismissed him. Woah, big mistake. The game never ended. All my pieces died, Medivh kept cheating and telling me to jump into the king to start the game. The exit door would not open. I hearthed out, reloaded ui, exited game completely, flew back, went back inside and I could tell the game was still going on, big letters on screen, \"Echo of Medivh cheat!\". lol. \r\nGood luck and don't dismiss anything.", "date": "2017-08-11T21:18:02-05:00", "rating": 8, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "this actually happens even if you use the exit button. has been happening for weeks. i made a bug report but it still happens now", "creationdate": "2017-08-16T03:10:11-05:00", "id": 1067323, "rating": 2, "commentid": 2513176, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "ossiferdown", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Yes. Solution is . don't dismiss the king, use Heroism on cd.", "creationdate": "2017-09-18T11:54:46-05:00", "id": 1075252, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2513176, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Shardsy", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Read somewhere else, don't remember where, that you have to disable your ElvUI. Works for me now without it.", "creationdate": "2017-10-26T15:00:30-05:00", "id": 1081666, "rating": 2, "commentid": 2513176, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "goldenpaww", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Disabling ElvUI worked for me. Additionally, to win the event, I never left the king. The old strat that was a sure thing failed me.", "creationdate": "2017-11-25T17:42:28-06:00", "id": 1086401, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2513176, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "piper", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 20, "id": 2513826, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Alystil", "body": "Chess Event is currently bugged. Pieces you dismiss vanish from the board. So when you start the event by hopping into the king and leave to move the pawns, the king is gone and with it your strongest piece. Worst of all, the king cannot die and therefor Echo of Medivh cannot win resulting in a broken instance. Resetting does not help as hunnib and others confirmed.\r\n\r\nSolution:\r\nI stayed in the king figure the whole time, buffing my other pieces with heroism and waited until the e2-pawn died to the enemy pawn. Then I was able to move my king. I then continued clearing the board and killing the war chief. Even fire on e1 did no significant damage. Just keep cool, buff and wait.", "date": "2017-08-16T06:29:09-05:00", "rating": 9, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "The issue is ElvUI; turn it off, works fine.", "creationdate": "2017-10-26T15:02:58-05:00", "id": 1081668, "rating": -1, "commentid": 2513826, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "goldenpaww", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I had this same bug, but I am not using ElvUi - using Dominos. Will try with disabling add on and see if that helps. Disabled one then all dominos and tried 10 other things to cause a reset of the raid to no avail. Submitted a ticket & waiting for help.... or Tuesday. :(", "creationdate": "2018-12-28T22:03:01-06:00", "id": 1212526, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2513826, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "PicklesForever", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 21, "id": 2519785, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Shardsy", "body": "The last weeks... the pawns disappear from the game when I dismiss them. I hope this is a passing bug.", "date": "2017-09-05T11:29:10-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 22, "id": 2532160, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "mcmelen", "body": "I took control of Warchief Blackhand to start the event. Dismissed the him and was teleported to the ramp. Took control of an Orc Necrolyte, spammed 4 while using the occasional heal. Eventually King Llane approached and killed him. I moved over one space to give myself more time to heal and attack. With no King of mine to kill, the event worked just fine. Assuming this would work for the Alliance.", "date": "2017-10-28T23:34:01-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I do absolutely the same thing. Usually King Llane is moving forward but he is being healed by a conjurer. As soon as conjurer is reachable I killed her (the one one the right). Than it's just King focus fire (Fireball and DOT). Blackhand is usually ok.", "creationdate": "2018-08-11T22:07:08-05:00", "id": 1127961, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2532160, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "kardanis", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2017-10-28T23:37:13-05:00", 1, "mcmelen"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 23, "id": 2534557, "nreplies": 6, "sticky": 0, "user": "Madalynn", "body": "This might get down voted but in the current patch I had issues with the chess event whilst trying to do it solo,  I have tried everything at one point and couldnt work out how to get this down solo, I even came here and looked up the patch and read the comments.\r\n\r\nI personally found in my experience the best way to beat this solo is to just Jump in your factions king Lane for alliance and Blackhand for horde and stay in there and press 4 for Bloodlust/heroism in hope that your king is the last one standing, I have tried moving around the pieces to no avail and I have tried staying in the king at least twice whilst pressing 4 for lust and this worked for me and I have managed to get past the chess event.\r\n\r\nI hope this will help others or you find your own way around this event to get it down.\r\n\r\nGoodluck have fun :)", "date": "2017-11-12T16:48:29-06:00", "rating": 35, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "This worked for me, thank you.", "creationdate": "2017-11-25T17:42:40-06:00", "id": 1086402, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2534557, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "piper", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Worked for me as well. As well, after the event ended I was still pacified, but when I entered Prowl the debuff dropped.", "creationdate": "2017-12-05T09:16:36-06:00", "id": 1088011, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2534557, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Izrili", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "This worked just made sure to move out of the fire. Nothing else worked for me being horde. Thanks!", "creationdate": "2018-03-24T19:48:38-05:00", "id": 1105648, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2534557, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "kc4vdx", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Chiming in that, after trying a number of strategies, this worked for me and was by far the easiest method.", "creationdate": "2018-08-12T18:14:32-05:00", "id": 1128233, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2534557, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "cuppscakes", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "What I need to know is, HOW do you reset? The bug made my King disappear, and now it won't end.", "creationdate": "2018-09-24T12:54:35-05:00", "id": 1146470, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2534557, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "MapleWarrior", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 24, "id": 2550393, "nreplies": 4, "sticky": 0, "user": "Plasmaxyz", "body": "If you are getting the bug where pieces disappear when you leave them, make sure you right click the buff to exit pieces. If you dismiss the unit you're in, it will always disappear.", "date": "2018-02-03T17:14:33-06:00", "rating": 51, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Thank you so much! I hadn't been able to finish this in so long and I couldn't figure out what the problem was. I was able to do it no problem now, thank you!!", "creationdate": "2018-02-21T23:51:25-06:00", "id": 1101211, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2550393, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Sawfty", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Thank you my king disappeared and now I can't reset the game. I even tried talking to Medivh.", "creationdate": "2018-04-24T22:32:50-05:00", "id": 1109786, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2550393, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Shancith", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "/reload ui will reset the game when it bugs", "creationdate": "2018-05-19T08:27:11-05:00", "id": 1112994, "rating": -5, "commentid": 2550393, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Thuugrim", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I've tried reload. Doesn't wok.", "creationdate": "2018-09-24T12:55:49-05:00", "id": 1146471, "rating": 2, "commentid": 2550393, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "MapleWarrior", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 25, "id": 2551992, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "MrGrubs", "body": "According to the patch notes, the 1-30-2018 hotfix adjusted the health of some pieces.  I won by taking control of the conjurer (queen) and focusing ranged attacks on the enemy king as soon as I could target him.  But first, I moved the king's footman (pawn) ahead one square, then moved the king ahead into the square vacated.  When Medivh cheated by creating fire under the king, I dropped control of the conjurer, took control of the king, and moved him out of the fire back one square to his original spot, then took control of the conjurer again.  The enemy healers simply cannot keep up with the conjurers focused fire due to this health change, but you have to control him or he will attack randomly.", "date": "2018-02-10T23:50:29-06:00", "rating": 31, "indent": 0, "roles": 16384, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I had tried a lot of various strategies listed here and the forums, but yours was the first to actually work for me. Thank you!", "creationdate": "2018-03-28T20:16:59-05:00", "id": 1106193, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2551992, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Marrra", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Still a great strategy after the great squish of 8.0.", "creationdate": "2018-07-29T21:12:15-05:00", "id": 1124632, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2551992, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Elysoun", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Excellent strategy", "creationdate": "2019-05-25T12:52:41-05:00", "id": 1302935, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2551992, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Berrenger", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 26, "id": 2573238, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "CyberChiewu", "body": "How to play: Once figured out, it makes sense.  But, the [b][Occupy a piece][i][/i][/b] button is not so intuitively obvious.   So, the first step is you're told to click on the King to start playing.  That's fine; but, first time there, figuring what to do next while learning what the piece has for spells, not so intuitive. Clicking the button [b][Occupy a piece][i][/i][/b] does not let you occupy a piece, and exiting the piece seems more like game over than the path to continued playing.\nBut this is one of those times when you can enter another vehicle.\n\nIntuitively, you'd think that would be obvious to just think of each piece as a vehicle, and it is, once you know that.  There is a short cool down when leaving one 'vehicle' before you're allowed to enter another.\n\nPerhaps the game's been changed again; but, as for winning, I found it so easy... I wondered what the fuss was about.  However, I will say it's easy to lose when one just sits in the King, and keeps pressing the occupy a piece trying to change pieces while in the king:  (\"What do you mean I need to be closer, I'm in the space next to him, how much closer can I get?)... Nevertheless, this little, really quite fun, game could have had better programming logistics and it would have really been fun, and maybe a tad more intuitive.  Ex: instead of having to leaving a piece to occupy another, allow the use of the occupy a piece button on the targeted piece (if it's yours), but only  if the current piece has all spells in cool down.  The cool down was so short when outside the piece, that just by increasing the cast time, they could have achieved the same result without having to leave and enter all the time, allowing for more continuity, making it more like real chess. They could also have made it more like real chess by allowing all pieces to move the number of squares like the original game.  The 'queen' does that to some degree, and the knight.... but the others... not so much.  Have fun... I sure did.\n\nOne last thing.  Be sure when done to reset the game.  Fail to do so and you'll soon discover that you can't use your spells or weapons because [spell=39331].  Just return to [npc=16816] and reset the game. However, it is one heck of a way to learn you're still playing, even if [b]you[/b] thought you were done.", "date": "2018-06-10T12:02:00-05:00", "rating": -10, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2018-06-10T12:45:52-05:00", 7, "CyberChiewu"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 27, "id": 2625752, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "adamfazai", "body": "BfA\r\nAfter so many weeks I ran just till Chess Event and didnt dare to do it.\r\nI finally did it in 1st run\r\n\r\nTry this:\r\n\r\nAs Horde: Jump On Blackhand, Do nothing except Bloodlust when enemies are near your troops.\r\nAfter a while Ally King came near, and I use no3 (cleave) on him and bloodlust on nearby guys.", "date": "2018-10-24T08:45:25-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Yes, this works, for either side. Move the three pawns in front of your king one space, and as much as possible control your king! Aside from moving it out of the fire as needed, you basically just stand there the whole time spamming its team damage ability.", "creationdate": "2018-11-16T03:24:25-06:00", "id": 1204983, "rating": -2, "commentid": 2625752, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Dust", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "yeah this didnt work at all lol", "creationdate": "2019-05-01T13:32:21-05:00", "id": 1300281, "rating": 2, "commentid": 2625752, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "rezzax", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "This didn't work for me either : (", "creationdate": "2020-07-15T19:14:31-05:00", "id": 1379435, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2625752, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "DeusExMchna", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
