{"commentv2": 1, "number": 33, "id": 3191822, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Incandio", "body": "This wretched encounter is still a buggy mess and frankly it says something about quality control at Blizzard that it hasn't been fixed, even after they had a fresh pass at it to make the chest lootable if you did somehow get lucky enough to complete the encounter.\n\nNot only does it glitch out constantly (pieces just vanishing after you exit them and so on) but there is no way to reset the encounter after it crashes, leaving you stranded and unable to progress.\n\nThe encounter doesn't even end when all your pieces are defeated, but just cycles through Medivh's \"cheating\" dialogue. Today I'm left with the silence debuff in KZ and the encounter still stuck on Medivh's dialogue even if I port out to Stormwind, reset all instances, then return. Will I ever be able to return to do this instance again? I'll return after the weekly reset.\n\nSo, still one to be avoided and ruining what should be the experience of running what used to be a flagship dungeon filled with lore.", "date": "2020-02-24T00:06:58-06:00", "rating": 12, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I want to second this so many times. Luckily the reset is tomorrow so I can take another crack it; horrible it's such a huge set of bugs on the single \"can't do anything else after this until it's complete\" fight.", "creationdate": "2020-06-01T15:57:58-05:00", "id": 1372504, "rating": 0, "commentid": 3191822, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "ConneurFM", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2020-02-24T00:31:36-06:00", 2, "Incandio"]}
